    <td bgcolor="#FFFFCC"><p>SIR, </p>
      <p>I received yours of yesterday, but cannot condescend to notice your insinuations. </p>
      <p>Your letter is not such as I had a right to expect from a member of Congress, with whom justice should never be disturbed by wanton passion, and by whom the public interest will never, I hope, be sacrificed to local prejudices or any disingenuous policy. </p>
      <blockquote>
        <p>I have the honor to be, yours, </p>
        <blockquote>
          <p>JAMES SMITH. </p>
        </blockquote>
    </blockquote>      </td>
